Public WithEvents oGroup As TagGroup Attribute oGroup.VB_VarHelpID = -1 Public otag As Tag
' Declare variables on screen load Private Sub Display_Load() Dim TagsInError As StringList Dim row_indx As Integer Set oGroup = Nothing Dim ArrayTag(0 To 30, 0 To 10) As Tag
Button2.Enabled = False
On Error GoTo errhandler If oGroup Is Nothing Then Set oGroup = Me.Application.CreateTagGroup(Me.AreaName, 500)
oGroup.Add "FileLoad\FilePath" Set otag = oGroup.Item("FileLoad\FilePath") otag.RefreshFromSource
oGroup.Active = True 'after setting tag group active, use RefreshFromSource() method before any tag reads or writes oGroup.RefreshFromSource TagsInError End If
GoTo OpenOk errhandler:
LogDiagnosticsMessage "VBA Error in SetUpTagGroup(). Error: " & Hex(Err.Number) & " - " & Err.Description, ftDiagSeverityError 'can add code to handle any specific errors Exit Sub
OpenOk:
Button2.Enabled = True
End Sub
Private Sub Button2_Released()
Dim TimeStamp As Date Dim cQuality As tagQualityConstants Dim cSubStatus As tagSubStatusConstants Dim cLimit As tagLimitConstants Dim s1 As String Dim file_name As String Dim fnum As Integer Dim File_Content As String Dim Temp_row As Variant Dim rows As Variant Dim num_cols As Long Dim num_rows As Long Dim FileArray() As String Dim R As Long Dim C As Long Dim row_indx As Integer Dim ArrayTag(0 To 30, 0 To 10) As Tag Dim RecIndex As Tag Dim LoadStatus As Tag Dim PartNo As Tag
Button2.Enabled = False Me.CommonDialog.Filter = "CSV File (*.csv)|*.CSV|All files (*.*)|*.*" Me.CommonDialog.DialogTitle = "Select File" Me.CommonDialog.CancelError = True On Error GoTo errhandler
Me.CommonDialog.ShowOpen
otag.Value = Me.CommonDialog.FileName
otag.GetTagData vValue, TimeStamp, cQuality, cSubStatus, cLimit otag.RefreshFromSource file_name = otag.Value 'Value otag.Value = Right(file_name, 50) fnum = FreeFile Open file_name For Input As fnum File_Content = Input$(LOF(fnum), #fnum) Close fnum
rows = Split(File_Content, vbCrLf) num_rows = UBound(rows) - 1 Temp_row = Split(rows(0), ",") num_cols = UBound(Temp_row) ReDim FileArray(num_rows, num_cols)
'Mem reserve for file loading into PLC registers oGroup.Add "{SYS_NUMBER_OF_PLYS}" oGroup.Add "{FileLoad\LoadProgress}" oGroup.Add "{PART_NUMBER}"
For row_indx = 0 To num_rows - 5 oGroup.Add ("{FileLoad\PlyID_" + Format(row_indx, "#0") + "}") oGroup.Add ("{FileLoad\Material_" + Format(row_indx, "#0") + "}") oGroup.Add ("{FileLoad\Stop_" + Format(row_indx, "#0") + "}") Next row_indx
'Load data into PLC registers
Set RecIndex = oGroup.Item("{SYS_NUMBER_OF_PLYS}") Set LoadStatus = oGroup.Item("{FileLoad\LoadProgress}") Set PartNo = oGroup.Item("{PART_NUMBER}")
For row_indx = 0 To num_rows - 5 Set ArrayTag(row_indx, 0) = oGroup.Item("{FileLoad\PlyID_" + Format(row_indx, "#0") + "}") Set ArrayTag(row_indx, 2) = oGroup.Item("{FileLoad\Material_" + Format(row_indx, "#0") + "}") Set ArrayTag(row_indx, 4) = oGroup.Item("{FileLoad\Stop_" + Format(row_indx, "#0") + "}") Next row_indx
'MsgBox "set array", vbOKOnly, "Value"
Temp_row = Split(rows(0), ",") PartNo.Value = Temp_row(1)
For R = 5 To num_rows Temp_row = Split(rows(R), ",")
ArrayTag(R - 5, 0).Value = Temp_row(0) ArrayTag(R - 5, 2).Value = Temp_row(2) ArrayTag(R - 5, 4).Value = Temp_row(4) Next R
'PLC mesages Number of records loaded and Status = 2 = recipe loaded successful
RecIndex.Value = num_rows - 4 LoadStatus.Value = 2
MsgBox "File Loaded", vbOKOnly, "Message"
Kill (file_name)
GoTo RoutineEnd
errhandler: If Err = cdlCancel Then MsgBox "Operation canceled, No file loaded", vbOKOnly, "Message" Else If Err.Number <> 0 Then Msg = "Error # " & Str(Err.Number) & " was generated by " & Err.Source & Chr(13) & Err.Description MsgBox Msg, vbOKOnly, "Error" End If End If
RoutineEnd:
Button2.Enabled = True
End Sub
